to break your ornament.

26:36.679 --> 26:38.014
VIC: Wayne!

26:41.768 --> 26:43.103
Wayne!

26:47.899 --> 26:51.402
Remember me, Wayne McQueen.

26:56.241 --> 26:58.451
- VIC: Wayne.
- Mom!

26:58.576 --> 27:01.496
Wayne! Wayne!

27:01.621 --> 27:03.289
You cannot just
run off like that.

27:03.414 --> 27:05.625
What are you thinking?
What?

27:08.920 --> 27:11.131
Why did you come out here?

27:11.256 --> 27:13.383
I don't know.

27:15.468 --> 27:17.762
How'd you know I'd be here?

27:19.722 --> 27:21.516
I don't know.
I just...

27:24.435 --> 27:25.436
Come on.

27:38.658 --> 27:40.702
[ Birds cawing]

27:54.174 --> 27:55.633
Dude.

28:01.222 --> 28:03.391
Oh, Jesus, look at this, Vicki.

28:03.516 --> 28:04.434
You're telling me

28:04.559 --> 28:06.352
we needed to pack this thing up
and bring it here?

28:06.477 --> 28:08.021
VIC: Yeah.

28:08.146 --> 28:09.939
That's from the old shovelhead.

28:13.026 --> 28:14.444
Harley ever ran.

28:14.569 --> 28:16.112
LINDA:
I hated that bike.

28:16.237 --> 28:18.198
[ Chuckles] I know.

28:19.240 --> 28:22.243
I have been cleaning up after
Chris McQueen my whole life

28:22.368 --> 28:23.953
and I am still doing it now.

28:24.078 --> 28:26.164
[Strurns note on guitar]

28:27.582 --> 28:29.876
You know I met him
when I was 12 years old?

28:33.046 --> 28:34.297
I miss him.

28:39.219 --> 28:41.554
He told me to forgive myself.

28:41.679 --> 28:43.306
- LINDA: Yeah.
-[ Scoffs ]

28:43.431 --> 28:47.143
Your dad was always good at
giving advice he couldn't take.

28:47.268 --> 28:49.729
It's hard advice
for a mother to follow.

28:49.854 --> 28:51.731
Did you?
[ Sniffles]

28:54.275 --> 28:56.361
I tell myself I have.

28:57.403 --> 28:59.072
And how'd you do it?

29:00.114 --> 29:01.824
I don't know.

29:06.913 --> 29:11.000
I used to resent how tightly
you held us, Dad and rne.

29:11.125 --> 29:14.337
I used to think
we'd just both...

29:14.462 --> 29:15.713
suffocate.

29:17.882 --> 29:18.883
But I --

29:21.678 --> 29:23.179
I get it now.

29:27.308 --> 29:28.768
How's Wayne?

29:31.479 --> 29:32.605
I don't know.
He's different, Ma.

29:32.730 --> 29:33.898
I just --
I don't --

29:37.902 --> 29:39.946
I don't know how to help him.

29:42.282 --> 29:45.743
LINDA:
What I regret with you

29:45.868 --> 29:50.832
is covering for your father,

29:50.957 --> 29:52.625
cleaning his messes.

29:52.750 --> 29:54.043
Maybe if --

29:55.503 --> 29:57.630
Maybe if we'd talked about
what was going on

29:57.755 --> 29:59.841
instead of pretending
it wasn't happening --

29:59.966 --> 30:01.592
I wouldn't've been
an alcoholic teenage morn

30:01.718 --> 30:03.344
and Wayne would be okay?

30:03.469 --> 30:06.431
Maybe it would've been
easier for you.

30:07.307 --> 30:09.767
And maybe
I could forgive myself.

30:13.938 --> 30:15.315
[Grunts]

30:15.440 --> 30:17.191
[ Chuckles ]

30:20.945 --> 30:22.572
I love you.

30:22.697 --> 30:24.449
Mwah.

30:26.576 --> 30:28.828
Stay here, Vicki, okay?

30:28.953 --> 30:30.246
Just for a little while.

30:30.371 --> 30:31.914
How can either of you get better

30:32.040 --> 30:34.334
living out there
where everything happened?

30:35.251 --> 30:37.754
You can even keep that Lou.

30:37.879 --> 30:39.464
[ Chuckles ]

30:52.852 --> 30:55.104
TABITHA: Some kids found it
in the Merrimack River

30:55.229 --> 30:56.647
close to the Pittman woods.

30:56.773 --> 30:59.025
Strange it turned up here
instead of Colorado.

31:00.610 --> 31:02.111
MAGGIE:
Not really.

31:02.236 --> 31:04.155
Christmasland was in
Charlie Manx's lnscape.

31:04.280 --> 31:05.907
The Shorter Way Bridge
was in Vic's.

31:09.202 --> 31:11.412
The Shorter Way
was here in Haverhill.

31:14.582 --> 31:17.001
My father helped demo it
when I was a kid.

31:24.008 --> 31:27.345
[ Machinery whirring ]

31:28.846 --> 31:30.681
What happened to the body?

31:31.682 --> 31:33.434
Cremated.

31:34.268 --> 31:36.521
[Alarm blaring ]

31:45.363 --> 31:47.240
No.

32:03.214 --> 32:05.049
It's over, Bats.

32:12.682 --> 32:14.809
It's all over.

32:14.934 --> 32:17.061
[Machinery grinding]

32:22.275 --> 32:24.485
[ Glass shattering ]

32:52.054 --> 32:53.764
[ Glass shatters ]

33:05.735 --> 33:09.155
MAGGIE: We really did it, Brat,
this time.

33:09.280 --> 33:11.657
Like, we stopped the Wraith,

33:11.782 --> 33:15.995
destroyed Christmasland,
saved those kids.

33:16.120 --> 33:18.289
Yeah, what's left of them.

33:18.414 --> 33:19.790
They're better off
with their families.

33:21.375 --> 33:23.169
Including Wayne.

33:24.337 --> 33:28.716
Lou is adopting him officially.

33:28.841 --> 33:30.092
Yeah.

33:33.346 --> 33:35.598
We're gonna stay in Haverhill
for awhile.

33:35.723 --> 33:38.100
Gunbarrel was Manx's home,
not ours,

33:38.226 --> 33:42.647
and it's -- it's --
it's bad for Wayne.

33:42.772 --> 33:43.940
He --

33:45.858 --> 33:47.985
It's bad for me, too, I think.

33:48.110 --> 33:52.615
Christmasland was Manx's home.

33:54.492 --> 33:59.080
The real question is,
what else is out there?

34:00.498 --> 34:04.502
How many other lnscapes
in the World of Thought?

34:04.627 --> 34:07.004
The Triumph's in storage.

34:07.129 --> 34:08.005
Well, let's go
take it out of storage.

34:08.130 --> 34:09.632
We're gonna stay here.

34:10.550 --> 34:14.719
In the Real World
with Wayne and -- and Lou.

34:17.056 --> 34:19.475
It's our happy ending, Maggie.
Try to see it.

34:19.600 --> 34:21.060
You're a Strong Creative.

34:21.185 --> 34:22.562
I can be creative
in this world, too.

34:22.687 --> 34:23.896
I started drawing again.

34:24.021 --> 34:26.315
You know that's not the same.

34:26.440 --> 34:28.609
I used to think that way.

34:28.734 --> 34:32.237
And, uh, it nearly got me
and my whole family killed.

34:35.741 --> 34:38.786
Vic, not every lnscape
is Christmasland.

34:38.911 --> 34:41.371
Think about Jolene's Tunnels.

34:42.206 --> 34:44.875
Your Bridge, yours.

34:45.001 --> 34:49.170
There is so much in this world
for us to explore.

34:49.297 --> 34:53.426
Crooked Alley, the Empty Forest.

34:53.551 --> 34:56.929
My Tiles have told me about
all kinds of places.

34:57.054 --> 35:00.224
Okay, and you know that they
came back to me for a reason.

35:01.559 --> 35:04.729
Yeah, the reason is that
Tabitha brought them to you.

35:11.402 --> 35:13.654
Just don't make her regret it.

35:35.968 --> 35:37.720
[ Knock on door]

35:37.845 --> 35:39.764
[ Door creaks ]

35:39.889 --> 35:41.223
Hey, kiddo.

35:42.600 --> 35:43.976
Supper's almost ready.

35:44.101 --> 35:45.144
Okay.

35:45.269 --> 35:47.438
One of the best things about
staying at Grandma's?

35:47.563 --> 35:49.523
Grandpa Sean's spaghetti sauce.

35:49.649 --> 35:51.942
Make a train
drive up a dirt road.

35:53.277 --> 35:55.488
When are we going home?

35:56.572 --> 35:57.948
Uh...

35:58.074 --> 36:00.493
We're gonna be staying here
for awhile, buddy.

36:01.577 --> 36:03.537
I miss my friends.

36:06.082 --> 36:08.501
I think you miss Christmasland.

36:08.626 --> 36:09.669
No.

36:13.297 --> 36:16.967
You know,
it's okay to talk about it.

36:21.097 --> 36:25.559
I used to miss Charlie Manx.

36:26.686 --> 36:31.440
I thought that, uh,
chasing him was -- was fun.

36:32.316 --> 36:36.904
Sometimes things that feel fun
aren't always good.

36:37.029 --> 36:39.198
Like having sugar for dinner.

36:39.323 --> 36:40.866
- LOU: Yeah.
- VIC: Mm.

36:44.537 --> 36:47.331
Are there other things
like that, Wayne?

36:55.548 --> 36:57.425
Look, it's okay if there are.

36:57.550 --> 36:59.719
Just, you know...

37:04.181 --> 37:05.433
- That's mine!
-lt's okay, Bats.

37:05.558 --> 37:07.268
Whatever it is, it's okay.

37:12.231 --> 37:14.817
I'm gonna look at it, alright?

37:40.760 --> 37:43.637
I think
there's something wrong with me.

37:43.763 --> 37:45.765
On the inside.

37:53.773 --> 37:57.902
It's okay to feel that way.

38:00.404 --> 38:05.117
You know, l-l feel that way
about myself all the time.

38:08.412 --> 38:13.501
That's why I --
l-| chased after Charlie Manx.

38:17.213 --> 38:19.548
It's why I drank too much.

38:20.382 --> 38:22.885
It's why I ran away
from you and Dad.

38:24.929 --> 38:29.600
Do you think maybe
that's why you ran away, too?

38:29.725 --> 38:32.102
Why you want to go back
to Christmasland?

38:36.857 --> 38:37.983
Hey.

38:38.984 --> 38:39.985
This?

38:40.110 --> 38:41.487
Coloring?

38:41.612 --> 38:44.990
Much better than doing
any of those other things.

38:46.575 --> 38:48.911
Even if the picture is scary?

38:49.036 --> 38:50.454
VIC:
Absolutely.

38:52.873 --> 38:54.291
Tell you what.

38:57.253 --> 39:00.756
No more running away
for either of us.

39:02.049 --> 39:03.133
Hmm?

39:04.844 --> 39:07.555
And no more pretending like
we feel okay when we don't.

39:07.680 --> 39:09.515
Dad included.

39:11.851 --> 39:14.353
Team McCarmody.
Alright?

39:14.478 --> 39:15.646
Yeah?

39:15.771 --> 39:17.815
We're staying
in the Real World, hmm?

39:28.868 --> 39:30.202
[Winces]

39:36.083 --> 39:38.460
How do I get
to the World of Thought?

39:46.468 --> 39:48.637
[ Tiles clatter]

39:58.939 --> 40:00.608
Hotel.

41:00.876 --> 41:03.379
[ Elevator music plays]

42:27.671 --> 42:29.923
[Engine shuts off]

42:30.049 --> 42:31.425
- Whoa.
-[ Chuckles ]

42:31.550 --> 42:33.719
- This is it.
- Yeah.

42:37.056 --> 42:38.932
This is where he used to live.

42:39.725 --> 42:40.768
Pretty creepy, huh?

42:40.893 --> 42:42.644
[ Chuckles] Yeah.

42:42.770 --> 42:44.938
You know,
Walter says it's haunted.

42:45.064 --> 42:47.566
-[ Chuckles ]
- Walter?

42:47.691 --> 42:49.485
You've been out here with him?

42:50.235 --> 42:51.195
What?

42:51.320 --> 42:53.572
No. No.

42:53.697 --> 42:55.115
C'mere.

43:03.207 --> 43:06.085
- Mm.
-[ Loud thump]

43:06.210 --> 43:07.544
- What was that?
- I don't know.

43:07.669 --> 43:09.838
- Is that a bear?
- I don't know.

43:09.963 --> 43:12.174
-[ Rustling ]
- Did you hear that?

43:12.966 --> 43:15.010
[Thump]

43:15.135 --> 43:16.720
What the hell?

43:22.392 --> 43:24.228
Wh--

43:24.353 --> 43:26.814
[ Eerie voice]
It's the ghost of Charlie Manx.

43:26.939 --> 43:28.273
Stop, stop.

43:28.398 --> 43:30.943
- And he's coming to kill us!
- Baby, stop, stop.

43:31.068 --> 43:32.611
-[Laughs]
- It's not funny.

43:32.736 --> 43:34.571
[ Both screaming ]
